# Jobio Backend Project Overview

## Project Description

Jobio Backend is a NestJS-based application following Clean Architecture principles with Domain-Driven Design (DDD). The project serves as a job recruitment platform backend with comprehensive company management, user authentication, and profile management capabilities.

## Technology Stack

- **Framework**: NestJS (Node.js)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL with Drizzle ORM
- **Authentication**: Supabase integration with JWT
- **Architecture**: Clean Architecture + DDD
- **Testing**: Jest with comprehensive test coverage
- **Documentation**: Swagger/OpenAPI
- **Event Handling**: Custom event-driven architecture

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── core/                    # Global foundational services
│   ├── validation/         # Input validation
│   ├── exceptions/         # Error handling
│   └── logger/            # Logging infrastructure
├── shared/                 # Common utilities and services
│   ├── application/       # Base classes (CQS, events)
│   ├── infrastructure/    # Database, pagination, utilities
│   └── domain/           # Shared domain models
├── lib/                    # Custom libraries
│   ├── drizzle-postgres/  # Database integration
│   ├── nest-event-driven/ # Event handling
│   ├── passport-supabase/ # Authentication strategies
│   └── flag-parser/       # Command line parsing
└── modules/                # Business domain modules
    ├── auth/              # Authentication & authorization
    ├── companies/         # Company management
    ├── user-context/      # User context management
